g.text: Credit scoring is a technique used to determine whether or not to extend credit (and if so, how much) to a borrower. This workflow illustrates how to create and choose a credit scoring model
based on both historical data and on the application of different machine learning algorithms.
Create a credit scoring model based on historical data. Select the best machine learning algorithm to be applied. Use cross-validation to evaluate model performance.
A use case is described at URL: https://www.knime.org/knime-applications/credit-scoring
